# Unrestricted Research API Guide
**Deep Research Across Google, Reddit, Twitter/X, and Social Media (2026)**

## Executive Summary

Finding truly **unrestricted** research APIs that aggregate Google articles, Reddit posts, Twitter/X, and other social media is challenging in 2026 because:

1. **Twitter/X shut down free API access** (February 2023) - now $42,000/year minimum
2. **Reddit moved to paid API** (April 2023) - protecting data from AI companies
3. **Most platforms now charge for data access** or actively block scrapers

**Best Solutions for Unrestricted Research**:

| Solution | Coverage | Restrictions | Cost | Best For |
|----------|----------|--------------|------|----------|
| **SERPGRID** | Google, Reddit, Twitter | None (uses Google index) | $49/mo | Best overall |
| **Firecrawl + Tavily** | Web + Deep search | None (scraping) | $20/mo + free | AI agents |
| **Apify** | All platforms | TOS gray area | $49/mo | Enterprise |
| **ScrapeCreators** | Social media | TOS gray area | Custom | High volume |
| **Jina AI Reader** | Any URL | None | Free (1M tokens) | URL conversion |

---

## üèÜ Winner: SERPGRID (Recommended)

**Website**: [serpgrid.dev](https://serpgrid.dev/)

**Why SERPGRID Wins**:
- **Accesses Reddit/Twitter through Google's index** (no platform API needed)
- **Completely unrestricted** - no content filtering
- **Real-time data** from Google SERP
- **No TOS violations** (uses public Google search)
- **Affordable** - $49/month for 10,000 searches

### SERPGRID Features

**Reddit Search API**:
```bash
curl -X POST https://api.serpgrid.com/reddit \
  -H "Authorization: Bearer YOUR_API_KEY" \
  -d '{
    "q": "quantum computing breakthroughs",
    "time_filter": "week",
    "subreddit": "science",
    "limit": 100
  }'
```

**Twitter/X Search API**:
```bash
curl -X POST https://api.serpgrid.com/twitter \
  -H "Authorization: Bearer YOUR_API_KEY" \
  -d '{
    "q": "AI regulation",
    "count": 500,
    "search_type": "recent"
  }'
```

**Google SERP API**:
```bash
curl -X POST https://api.serpgrid.com/search \
  -H "Authorization: Bearer YOUR_API_KEY" \
  -d '{
    "q": "cybersecurity zero-day exploits",
    "location": "United States",
    "google_domain": "google.com"
  }'
```

**Pricing**:
```
Starter: $49/month (10,000 searches)
Pro: $99/month (30,000 searches)
Enterprise: Custom pricing
```

**Key Benefits**:
- ‚úÖ No Reddit API restrictions
- ‚úÖ No Twitter API restrictions
- ‚úÖ Uses Google's public index (legal)
- ‚úÖ Real-time data
- ‚úÖ No content filtering
- ‚úÖ Structured JSON output

