## üîß Tool #4: Jina AI Reader API (URL Converter)

**Website**: [jina.ai/reader](https://jina.ai/reader/)

**What It Does**:
- **Converts any URL to LLM-friendly Markdown**
- **No API key required** for basic usage
- **Free for 1 million tokens/month**
- **Handles JavaScript-heavy sites**

**Usage**:
```bash
# Simply prepend URL with r.jina.ai
curl https://r.jina.ai/https://reddit.com/r/programming/comments/xyz123

# Returns clean Markdown of entire thread
```

**API Example**:
```python
import requests

url = "https://twitter.com/elonmusk/status/123456789"
response = requests.get(f"https://r.jina.ai/{url}")

markdown_content = response.text
# Feed to your LLM for analysis
```

**Use Cases**:
```
1. Reddit thread analysis
2. Twitter thread scraping
3. News article extraction
4. Documentation scraping
5. Forum post collection
```

**Pricing**:
```
Free: 1M tokens/month (no API key)
Pro: $20/month (10M tokens)
Enterprise: Custom
```

**MCP Integration** (DIY):
```javascript
// Create custom MCP tool
{
  "name": "jina_reader",
  "description": "Convert any URL to Markdown",
  "parameters": {
    "url": { "type": "string", "description": "URL to convert" }
  }
}

// Implementation
async function jinaReader(url) {
  const response = await fetch(`https://r.jina.ai/${url}`);
  return await response.text();
}
```

