## Implementation Guide

### Step 1: Sign Up for SERPGRID

```bash
# 1. Visit serpgrid.dev
# 2. Sign up (free trial available)
# 3. Get API key from dashboard
# 4. Test Reddit search

curl -X POST https://api.serpgrid.com/reddit \
  -H "Authorization: Bearer YOUR_API_KEY" \
  -d '{
    "q": "AI tools",
    "limit": 10
  }'
```

### Step 2: Install Firecrawl MCP

```bash
# Get Firecrawl API key
# Visit firecrawl.dev ‚Üí Sign up ‚Üí Get key

# Add to Roo Code settings.json
{
  "mcpServers": {
    "firecrawl": {
      "command": "npx",
      "args": ["-y", "@firecrawl/mcp-server"],
      "env": {
        "FIRECRAWL_API_KEY": "fc-YOUR-KEY"
      }
    }
  }
}
```

### Step 3: Add Tavily MCP

```bash
# Get Tavily API key
# Visit tavily.com ‚Üí Sign up (no CC) ‚Üí Get key

# Add to Roo Code settings.json
{
  "mcpServers": {
    "tavily": {
      "command": "npx",
      "args": ["-y", "@tavily/mcp-server"],
      "env": {
        "TAVILY_API_KEY": "tvly-YOUR-KEY"
      }
    }
  }
}
```

### Step 4: Create SERPGRID MCP Tool (Custom)

Create `~/.claude/serpgrid-mcp-server.js`:

```javascript
#!/usr/bin/env node
import { McpServer } from '@modelcontextprotocol/sdk/server/mcp.js';
import { StdioServerTransport } from '@modelcontextprotocol/sdk/server/stdio.js';
import { z } from 'zod';

const SERPGRID_API_KEY = process.env.SERPGRID_API_KEY;
const SERPGRID_BASE_URL = 'https://api.serpgrid.com';

const server = new McpServer({
  name: 'serpgrid',
  version: '1.0.0'
});

// Reddit search tool
server.tool(
  'serpgrid_reddit_search',
  'Search Reddit threads via Google index',
  {
    query: z.string().describe('Search query'),
    subreddit: z.string().optional().describe('Specific subreddit'),
    time_filter: z.enum(['hour', 'day', 'week', 'month', 'year', 'all']).optional(),
    limit: z.number().default(20)
  },
  async ({ query, subreddit, time_filter, limit }) => {
    const response = await fetch(`${SERPGRID_BASE_URL}/reddit`, {
      method: 'POST',
      headers: {
        'Authorization': `Bearer ${SERPGRID_API_KEY}`,
        'Content-Type': 'application/json'
      },
      body: JSON.stringify({ q: query, subreddit, time_filter, limit })
    });

    const data = await response.json();
    return { content: [{ type: 'text', text: JSON.stringify(data, null, 2) }] };
  }
);

// Twitter search tool
server.tool(
  'serpgrid_twitter_search',
  'Search Twitter/X posts via Google index',
  {
    query: z.string().describe('Search query'),
    count: z.number().default(50),
    search_type: z.enum(['recent', 'popular']).optional()
  },
  async ({ query, count, search_type }) => {
    const response = await fetch(`${SERPGRID_BASE_URL}/twitter`, {
      method: 'POST',
      headers: {
        'Authorization': `Bearer ${SERPGRID_API_KEY}`,
        'Content-Type': 'application/json'
      },
      body: JSON.stringify({ q: query, count, search_type })
    });

    const data = await response.json();
    return { content: [{ type: 'text', text: JSON.stringify(data, null, 2) }] };
  }
);

// Google SERP tool
server.tool(
  'serpgrid_google_search',
  'Search Google SERP',
  {
    query: z.string().describe('Search query'),
    location: z.string().optional().default('United States'),
    num_results: z.number().default(10)
  },
  async ({ query, location, num_results }) => {
    const response = await fetch(`${SERPGRID_BASE_URL}/search`, {
      method: 'POST',
      headers: {
        'Authorization': `Bearer ${SERPGRID_API_KEY}`,
        'Content-Type': 'application/json'
      },
      body: JSON.stringify({ q: query, location, num: num_results })
    });

    const data = await response.json();
    return { content: [{ type: 'text', text: JSON.stringify(data, null, 2) }] };
  }
);

const transport = new StdioServerTransport();
await server.connect(transport);
```

**Add to Roo Code**:
```json
{
  "mcpServers": {
    "serpgrid": {
      "command": "node",
      "args": ["${HOME}/.claude/serpgrid-mcp-server.js"],
      "env": {
        "SERPGRID_API_KEY": "${SERPGRID_API_KEY}"
      }
    }
  }
}
```

